  "prompt": "What is the amount of Maximum cash deposit in a saving bank account in a single financial year in India?",
  "response": "In India, there is no specific limit on the maximum amount of cash that can be deposited in a savings bank account in a single financial year. However, large cash deposits may attract scrutiny from the Income Tax Department and could potentially require the depositor to provide an explanation for the source of funds, especially if the amount is substantial or seems inconsistent with the depositor's known financial profile.\n\nAs per current regulations, banks are required to report cash deposits exceeding Rs. 10 lakh in a financial year to the Income Tax Department. Additionally, as part of anti-money laundering and counter-terrorism financing measures, banks must report any suspicious transactions that may arise from large or inconsistent cash deposits.\n\nIt's always advisable to maintain proper records and documentation for any significant cash transactions to ensure compliance with tax laws and banking regulations.",
